In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 22, 2015, as National Voter Registration Day. He emphasizes the importance of voting as a fundamental right and a key aspect of democracy. The President encourages all eligible Americans to register to vote and participate in shaping the future of the country. He acknowledges that government efforts alone are not enough, and it is the responsibility of individual citizens to exercise their right to vote. The article also highlights the relatively low voting rates in the United States and the need for increased engagement in the political process. President Obama calls on Americans to honor the legacy of liberty and self-government by registering to vote and encouraging others to do the same.